## March

March brought a subtle shift in guidance. On March 4th, [Te Whatu Ora](/Te_Whatu_Ora) (Health New Zealand) advised that household contacts of positive cases no longer needed daily testing unless symptomatic. This coincided with 164 new cases reported, and a seven-day rolling average of 796 per day. A new, updated COVID-19 vaccine, designed to tackle newer strains, was released on March 7th. Hospitalizations stood at 171 on March 11th, with the seven-day average at 686. By March 18th, hospitalizations had significantly decreased to 55, with the average at 667.

