## September

September saw a continued decline in reported cases and deaths. By September 16th, only 728 new cases and 3 deaths were recorded. Hospitalizations were minimal, with 64 COVID-19 positive individuals in hospital as of September 15th. A study published in the [New Zealand Medical Journal](/New_Zealand_Medical_Journal) on September 6th indicated sustained vaccine effectiveness against hospitalization and death, though effectiveness against infection waned over time.

