## October

October saw the cessation of free COVID-19 rapid antigen tests (RATs) from the 1st of the month, a decision that sparked concern from Dr [Michael Baker](/Michael_Baker_(epidemiologist)) regarding its potential impact on lower-income communities, particularly [Māori](/M%C4%81ori_people) and [Pasifika New Zealanders](/Pasifika_New_Zealanders). The XEC sub-variant was reported to have arrived in New Zealand. Hospitalizations hovered around 89 to 106 throughout the month. Dr Baker also issued a warning about a potential summer wave of infections and deaths.

