## November

November saw a slight uptick in new cases, with 1,675 reported on November 25th. Hospitalizations remained relatively low, ranging from 76 to 85. On November 28th, the government released the report from the first phase of the [Royal Commission of Inquiry into COVID-19 Lessons Learned](/Royal_Commission_of_Inquiry_into_COVID-19_Lessons_Learned), a document that likely contained as much bureaucratic jargon as genuine insight.

